The '''Temple of Mercury''' was a Roman sanctuary in [[Puy de Dôme]], dedicated to [[Mercury (mythology)|Mercury]].<ref>Alain Tourreau, De la Chaîne des Puys au volcan de Jaude, Éditions Créer, Collection Patrimoine, 2002, ({{ISBN|978-2909797625}}), p. 57</ref> It was a significant regional cult center.
The temple was founded during the 1st century and active until at least the 3rd century. Since 1875, substantial excavations has been made on the site.
